name: Dystopia | Status-quo
description:
Authorities will always try to survive in various kinds of crises, because they live from crises that they create themselves.  all the policies they make always bring unstable consequences.  This unstableness is what makes them preventive for their own sake.

This natural contradiction was predicted by Karl Marx who stated that "that the life of capitalism will self-destruct because of the contradictions built up in it".  

Dystopia is the self-destruction.
Inevitable consequences.
